A man has been taken to hospital after a fire broke out in the kitchen of a flat in Glasgow east end. Man in hospital after kitchen fire at Dennistoun flat A man has been taken to hospital after a fire broke out in the kitchen of a flat in Glasgow east end.
Crews were called to the four-storey block in Walter Street, Dennistoun, at 17:55 on Thursday.
Firefighters wearing breathing apparatus extinguished the blaze.
The man was treated at the scene for the effects of smoke inhalation before being taken by ambulance to nearby Glasgow Royal Infirmary.
 